Text.Value: I am glad thou art ready. Thou may have good reason to be.
A true leader. Thou understood the value of communion and companionship, and the enduring bonds of those who share love and loss.
Thy wizard, Gale.
Thou art not above recognising the improbable nature of thy success.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
Well met. Settle thyself. We have much to discuss.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [gj] Party gathers around to sit near a campfire, finding their respective seats around the fire
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We see Withers, the player, and the companions in their party gathering around a campfire and taking their seats.

Text.Value: Its pursuit of freedom drove thee to thy own.
Thou answered me:
Her sacrifice was great indeed. No doubt thou will hold space for her. As she held space for thee.
His sacrifice was great indeed.
Thou did well to survive.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
My life is a lot more dull now that there isn't a world to save.
Nothing, I hope. I think I'll retire.
And this time, I'm sorry to say, there's no coming back.
I miss it dearly.
And if it hath, then thou might suppose its story is concluded, that the mind flayer is... happy.
Karlach. She made the ultimate sacrifice, just so we wouldn't have to.
And thy companions, too.
I wonder what became of it?
Tell me - what hast thou done with thyself since we last convened?
Thou need not worry.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
Thy actions have altered the very fabric of fate.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
One might suppose it hath returned to that life.
Tell me - what was thy secret? The source of thy power, the seed of thy triumph?
The Emperor. I couldn't have done any of this without it.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
Fate's fabric spins on a neverending loom.
One's standards once raised are not easily lowered, are they?
I just did what I set out to do - I cured myself of the parasite in my head.
But there is another who had no small part to play.
I asked thee once: what is the worth of a single mortal life.
Tell me - what fate awaits thee? What new adventures?
That its value is as currency.
That it depends upon a person's deeds.
Thou hast achieved much with thine since then.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
I would not have survived without the help of friends and allies.
But thou need not surrender to tedium.
That each is of infinite value and merits, worthy of sacrificing everything.
And the loss of one in particular, who had no small part to play.
The same may not be said for thy wizard, Gale.
Thy mind flayer and thee did grow rather attached.
Truly, I wish I could be there with you.
He defied the gods to answer to his own.
Gale. He sacrificed himself so that we could all live.
Hard graft, and endurance. It was quite a fight from start to finish.
Thou did not ask for its presence in thy life. And yet thou recognises that thou could not have done without it.
Thou did share a most unusual bond. A bond I daresay none have ever seen the likes of.
Thou, who art but a mortal.
It had a life before it met thee - a life that gave it purpose.
But no tears, friends. I hope that my sacrifice was meaningful - that the world is a safer place, and that you have found happiness.
His people will continue the war in his name. And thine.
Thy services may yet be required.
Well met! I am a magical projection of Gale of Waterdeep, and if you see this manifestation, that means I have prematurely perished.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
Orpheus. He became the very thing he loathed, to save his people and his legacy.
Well put, and earnestly spoken.
There's no secret. It was easy.
But now, I voyage elsewhere, on unknown currents, through unknown realms. One with the Weave. One with the infinite.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hologram fades out into astral/Weave/infinite space.

Text.Value: And now thy story marches on, as inevitable as time itself.
Thou who dared die to defy Bhaal. I see the goodly cure has kept you well.
Though his body hath departed us, he did leave thee one parting message.
But thy story marches on, as inevitable as time itself.
Thus, is his story ended. His life bequeathed unto his god.
I don't know yet, but I'm sure something will show up.
|Reflection on the fact that Gale blew himself up to save everyone.|
Thou felled three Chosen and a Netherbrain, and in so doing prevented the fall of Baldur's Gate.
That it matters not, outside of thine own.
Thy focus is impressive. Thou didst not lose sight of thy purpose. Even in the face of distraction and despair.
Rest, fill thy will. Take thy peace where thou can get it.
Thou art confident. Thou hast reason to be. Thou hast accomplished much.
Thou who failed thy Father, and whose mind has all but been consumed...
Thou wilt do well to sustain thy energy and thy curiosity in this vein.
It was a necessary evil. But I sleep a lot better without its voice in my head.
That its worth is in the legends that remember it.
Every day is an adventure, if you live it right.
An individual of no less strength of character and will than thee.
Thou not without thy losses. I speak of thy wizard, Gale.

Synopsis: 6 months later after saving Baldur's Gate, Withers gathers the companions and player around a campfire to invite them to recollect what they've been doing.
